h3. Issue Summary

Links to files/images in comments are broken while sending an email using Automation
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an automation rule that is triggered when a comment is added
 # Add an action that sends an email with the comment like
{noformat}
{{#issue.comments.reverse}}
    {{body.html}}
{{/}}
{noformat}

 # Save the rule and add a comment on a ticket with an image.

h3. Expected Results

The comments are sent over along with attachments.
h3. Actual Results

The links are invalid and users can't access the attachment via email. Right below follows an example of the link that is sent via email:
{noformat}
img src="/secure/attachment/ID/NAME
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

We can use the following regex to exclude images from the comment:
{noformat}
{{#issue.comments.reverse}}  
   {{body.replaceAll("![^\s!][^!]+[^\s!]+[!]", " ")}} 
{{/}}
{noformat}
ps. If we use the regex above we can't convert the comment from Wiki to HTML.

It seems that the project dropdown/picker is limited to a hardcoded value of 250px which is too small for bigger instances where projects name prefix could be identical for more than 250px.

Same UX bug affects other similar dropdowns in the application but this one is clearly the easiest to spot.

There is an already documented workaround for Jira Server but that's was supposed to be only temporary until Atlassian implements a properfix.
{code:java}
 #issuetype-single-select, #project-single-select, form.aui .aui-ss, .jiraform .aui-ss,
    form.aui .text, form.aui .password, form.aui .textarea, form.aui .select, form.aui .multi-select, form.aui .aui-select2-container .select2-choices {
        max-width: 500px !important;
    }
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

Calling {{POST /rest/api/3/jql/match}} with assignee in JQL (like {{assignee = Vitaliy Ushanov}}) returns no matches when {{POST /rest/api/3/search}} shows the JQL should match.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # User “Vitaliy Ushanov” in Jira is assigned to the issue with id 10618. Replace user name and issue id in steps below.
 # POST to the [search|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-issue-search/#api-rest-api-3-search-post] api with body:
{code:json}
{
  "expand": [
    "names"
  ],
  "jql": "assignee = \"Vitaliy Ushanov\"",
  "maxResults": 15,
  "fieldsByKeys": false,
  "fields": [
    "assignee"
  ],
  "startAt": 0
}
{code}
Confirm results in json similar to:
{code:json}
{
    "expand": "schema,names",
    "startAt": 0,
    "maxResults": 15,
    "total": 27,
    "issues": [
        {
            "expand": "operations,versionedRepresentations,editmeta,changelog,renderedFields",
            "id": "10618",
            ...
{code}
Note the first issue found.
 # POST to the [match|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-issue-search/#api-rest-api-3-jql-match-post] api with body (using the same jql and the issue noted from first step above):
{code:json}
{
    "issueIds": [
	10618
    ],
    "jqls": [
	"assignee = \"Vitaliy Ushanov\""
    ]
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results

The expected result is the issue matches similar to:
{code:json}
{
    "matches": [
        {
            "matchedIssues": [
                10618
            ],
            "errors": []
        }
    ]
}
{code}

h3. Actual Results

The actual result is no matches are found.
{code:json}
{
    "matches": [
        {
            "matchedIssues": [],
            "errors": []
        }
    ]
}
{code}
Single quotes in name (‘Vitaliy Ushanov’) don’t help.

h3. Workaround

Replace full user name in jql by its id in request body:
{code:json}
{
    "issueIds": [
	10618
    ],
   "jqls": [
	"assignee = 5d2f56472d76f30c36bf88ce"
    ]
}
{code}
Now the match result is correct and the issue with id 10618 is found:
{code:json}
{
    "matches": [
        {
            "matchedIssues": [
                10618
            ],
            "errors": []
        }
    ]
}
{code}
The problem with this as "workaround" is this isn't the actual JQL that works in both UI and search API.

